  "description": "A resource that can be bound to a bind group and used in a shader. Whilst a buffer can be used as a resource, this class allows you to specify an offset and size of the buffer to use. This is useful if you have a large buffer and only part of it is used in a shader. This resource, will listen for changes on the underlying buffer and emit a itself if the buffer changes shape. const buffer = new Buffer({ data: new Float32Array(1000), usage: BufferUsage.UNIFORM, }); // Create a buffer resource that uses the first 100 bytes of a buffer const bufferResource = new BufferResource({ buffer, offset: 0, size: 100, });",
